============
 Filecatman 
============

A file categorization management program, designed to make sorting, categorizing and accessing data simple and easy.

Homepage: https://github.com/fcmadmin/filecatman

Author: Rich T

==========================
Installation Instructions:
==========================

For detailed instructions see the documentation in the ‘docs’ folder.

Install and run from venv (recommended):
(requires python3.10+)
	Linux in terminal:
		1. $ python -m venv ./venv
		2. $ source venv/bin/activate
		3. $ pip install .
		4. $ filecatman
	Windows in admin CMD:
		1. $ python -m venv .\venv
		2. $ .\venv\Scripts\activate
		3. $ pip install .
		4. $ filecatman
	Mac in terminal:
		1. $ python -m venv ./venv
		2. $ source venv/bin/activate
		3. $ pip install .
		4. $ filecatman

Or install to system:
	New Linux method (requires pip and python 3.10+):
		1. $ sudo pip install .
		2. $ filecatman
	Deprecated Linux method (requires setuptools):
		1. $ python3 setup.py build
		2. $ sudo python3 setup.py install
		3. $ sudo python3 setup.py install_data
		4. $ filecatman
	Windows in admin CMD (requires python 3.10+):
		1. $ pip install .
		2. (add the installation directory to the Windows PATH)
		3. $ filecatman
	Mac in terminal (requires python 3.10+):
		1. $ sudo python -m pip install .
		2. $ filecatman

Or run from source:
	1. $ pip install -r requirements.txt
	2. $ python maindev.py

